#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:320
msgid "Enabled signals"
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:321
msgid "Signals that depend on an extension are hidden automatically if that extension is inactive or there is not enough data. Response time and rate thresholds are configurable below. Signals are omitted rather than estimated."
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:329
msgid "Response rate grace period (hours)"
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:330
msgid "Conversations opened within this many hours are left out of the response rate, so a brand-new unanswered message does not lower a vendor's rate before they have had a fair chance to reply. Default: 48."
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:339
msgid "Minimum response rate to display (%)"
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:340
msgid "The response rate is only shown when it is at least this percentage, so a low rate is not advertised on the vendor's own page. Set to 0 to always show it. Default: 80."
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:349
msgid "Slowest response time to display (days)"
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:350
msgid "The response time signal is hidden entirely when a vendor's typical first reply is slower than this many days. The displayed wording always comes from the true value (within an hour, a day, a few days, a week, two weeks, a month), so whatever is shown reads true at any setting. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:359
msgid "Minimum conversations"
msgstr ""

#: hivepress-trust-signals.php:360
msgid "Response time and rate are only shown once a vendor has received at least this many conversations."
msgstr ""

